<p>In a registration form I the username should only contain a-z A-Z 0-9 underscore, dashes, and dots. So I have defined a custom validator in the boot method of AppServiceProvider as follows;</p>  <pre><code>Validator::extend('valid_username', function ($attribute, $value, $parameters)             {                     return preg_match('[a-zA-Z0-9_\-\.]', $value);             } </code></pre>  <p>But the validation never passes. what I'm doing wrong?</p>